\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\i0\fs32 1.\f1  What is JavaScript? \par
\f0\lang16393 answer=    JavaScript is a scripting or programming language that allows you to implement complex features on web pages \f1\emdash  every time a web page does more than just sit there and display static information for you to look at \emdash  displaying timely content updates, interactive maps, animated 2D/3D graphics, scrolling video jukeboxes, etc. \emdash  you can bet that JavaScript is probably involved. It is the third layer of the layer cake of standard web technologies, two of which (HTML and CSS) we have covered in much more detail in other parts of the Learning Area.\par
\f0 =====================================================\par
2.\f1\bullet  What is the use of isNaN function?\par
\f0 answer=  In Javascript NaN stands for "Not-a-Number". Hence here, isNaN() is a method in Javascript used to check whether a value is a number or not.\par
The method isNaN in JavaScript returns true if the given value is Not-a-Number, else it returns false.\par
